    <!-- Main Content -->
    <main class="main">
        <section class="page-hero">
            <div class="container">
                <h1>How to Use There's Something About AI</h1>
                <p>Get the most out of our AI comparison platform</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="content-section">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="instructions-content">
                    <div class="instruction-step">
                        <div class="step-number">1</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h2>Enter Your Prompt</h2>
                            <p>Start by typing your question or prompt in the text area on the home page. Be specific and clear about what you want to know. Good prompts lead to better comparisons.</p>
                            <div class="example-box">
                                <strong>Good Example:</strong> "Explain the concept of machine learning and provide three real-world applications."
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="instruction-step">
                        <div class="step-number">2</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h2>Submit and Wait</h2>
                            <p>Click the "Compare AI Responses" button to send your prompt to three different AI engines: GPT-4, Claude, and Gemini. The platform will process your request and generate responses from each AI.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="instruction-step">
                        <div class="step-number">3</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h2>Review the Results</h2>
                            <p>You'll be taken to the results page where you can see all three AI responses side by side. Each response is clearly labeled with the AI engine that generated it.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="instruction-step">
                        <div class="step-number">4</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h2>Compare Responses</h2>
                            <p>Use the comparison buttons to focus on specific AI pairs:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>AI 1 vs AI 2:</strong> Compare GPT-4 and Claude responses</li>
                                <li><strong>AI 1 vs AI 3:</strong> Compare GPT-4 and Gemini responses</li>
                                <li><strong>AI 2 vs AI 3:</strong> Compare Claude and Gemini responses</li>
                                <li><strong>Show All:</strong> View all three responses together</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="instruction-step">
                        <div class="step-number">5</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h2>Analyze Differences</h2>
                            <p>The differences section at the bottom highlights key variations between the AI responses, including approach, detail level, and perspective. This helps you understand how each AI interprets and responds to your prompt.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="instruction-step">
                        <div class="step-number">6</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h2>Try New Prompts</h2>
                            <p>Use the prompt input at the bottom of the results page to try new questions without returning to the home page. Your prompt history is saved for easy access to previous queries.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="tips-section">
                    <h2>Tips for Better Results</h2>
                    <div class="tips-grid">
                        <div class="tip-card">
                            <h3>Be Specific</h3>
                            <p>Clear, specific prompts yield more useful comparisons. Include context and specify the type of response you're looking for.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tip-card">
                            <h3>Try Different Types</h3>
                            <p>Experiment with various prompt types: questions, creative tasks, analysis requests, and problem-solving scenarios.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tip-card">
                            <h3>Look for Patterns</h3>
                            <p>Notice how different AIs consistently approach certain types of questions. This helps you choose the right AI for your needs.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tip-card">
                            <h3>Use History</h3>
                            <p>Access your prompt history from the dropdown menu to revisit and refine previous queries.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
